<TEXT>
prime minister toshiki kaifu will travel to the 
united states to meet with president bush next month the japanese 
government announced thursday 
an official in the ministry of foreign affairs said kaifu will 
meet with president bush in washington on sept 1 the government 
has not yet confirmed details of the trip 
foreign minister taro nakayama will accompany kaifu said the 
official who spoke on condition of anonymity 
at the meeting kaifu will reaffirm his governments commitment 
to maintaining good relations with the united states the official 
said 
this will be the first time for the two leaders to meet and also 
kaifus first meeting with a foreign leader since becoming prime 
minister on aug 9 
the 58yearold kaifu took japans highest office after sousuke 
uno stepped down to take responsibility for the governing liberal 
democrats crushing setback in parliamentary elections last month 
a us embassy official speaking on condition of anonymity said 
president bush will interrupt a holiday at his home in 
kennebunkport maine to meet with kaifu 
</TEXT>
