<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the major events involving ptl and jim 
bakker since his resignation as head of the fort mill scbased 
ministry and its heritage usa christian theme park 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
march 19 bakker resigns amid sex and money scandal involving 
former new york church secretary jessica hahn the rev jerry 
falwell takes over as chairman of the board and richard dortch 
becomes president of ptl 
may 6 assemblies of god leaders defrock bakker and dortch 
june 12 ptl files for protection from creditors under chapter 
11 of the us bankruptcy code 
oct 8 falwell the ptl board of directors the cohosts of the 
ptl show and other top executives resign from ptl during a 
dispute over bankruptcy reorganization plan and fears that bakker 
will be allowed to return david clark a christian broadcasting 
network executive becomes trustee 
dec 22 us bankruptcy judge rufus reynolds approves the 
ministrys bankruptcy plan which divides ptl into separate 
ministerial and forprofit entities and involves a schedule for 
repaying creditors 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 31 ptl sues bakker and his chief aide david taggart for 
52 million for recovery of unwarranted compensation and funds lost 
through mismanagement 
april 22 the irs revokes ptls taxexempt status 
may 20 clark resigns as ptl trustee to become president of 
heritage ministries the nonprofit ministerial entity former 
winstonsalem nc mayor mc benton becomes the new trustee 
clark later resigns as president of heritage ministries 
june 7 jim and tammy bakker return from california open an 
office for jim and tammy ministries and move into a condominium paid 
for by supporters 
aug 31 bakker and benton agree on terms for bakker to buy 
heritage usa paving the way for bakkers return as leader of ptl 
sept 9 bakker misses deadline for 3 million deposit benton 
says he will no longer negotiate with bakker 
nov 3 us attorney charles alexander notifies the bakkers and 
taggart they are subjects of a grand jury investigation 
nov 10 reynolds rules that the bakkers and taggart must pay 
76 million in damages to ptl 
dec 5 federal grand jury hands up indictments of bakker and 
dortch on charges of mail fraud and wire fraud they also are 
accused of conspiring to defraud ministry contributors to support 
extravagant lifestyles and of diverting more than 4 million in ptl 
money for their personal benefit bakker aides james and david 
taggert are charged with evading taxes conspiring to impede the irs 
in tax collection and using more than 11 million in ptl money for 
personal expenditures 
dec 13 toronto real estate magnate stephen mernick an 
orthodox jew buys the assets of ptl for 65 million at a hearing 
before judge reynolds 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
january the bakkers begin broadcasting the jim and tammy 
show from their leased home in charlotte 
feb 13 mernick assumes joint management of the heritage usa 
property with a bankruptcy trustee but title questions delay the 
sales closing 
march 29 bakker arrives at a florida retreat for ministers but 
continues to tape his program bakker had to cease his broadcasts 
from his charlotte home since they violated zoning ordinances 
may 8 the bakkers broadcast the jim and tammy show live 
from their new studio in a boardedup department store in a nearly 
abandoned mall in southwest orlando fla 
july 25 the taggart brothers are convicted of tax evasion 
charges 
aug 8 dortch agrees to plead guilty four counts mail fraud 
wire fraud by telephone wire fraud by television and conspiracy 
and testify against bakker 
</TEXT>
