by ignoring jewish suffering in speeches and comments about that era 
the holocaust is at the root of the latest dispute which 
involves a carmelite convent at oswiecim poland a few feet from 
the fence surrounding the auschwitz concentration camp 
jewish groups say the convent and its christian symbols such as 
a 23foot cross offend the memory of the 25 million jews who died 
there 
under an accord signed by catholic and jewish leaders in 1987 
the nuns were supposed to have moved by feb 22 to a prayer center 
to be built several thousand yards away 
the deadline passed and the center has yet to be built jewish 
groups accused the polish church of reneging 
what was supposed to be and should have been a discreet and 
loving gesture of conciliation and reconciliation because of delays 
has become a stumbling block on the path of jewishcatholic 
relations said tullia zevi president of the union of italian 
jewish communities and a signatory to the 1987 accord 
after a series of demonstrations at the convent by american 
jewish activists cardinal franciszek macharski announced aug 10 he 
was suspending the agreement to move the nuns he blamed western 
jewish groups for launching a violent campaign of accusations and 
slanders and creating an atmosphere of aggressive demands 
many jews want the pope to intervene 
the pope himself sparked a controversy with his remarks during 
two recent general audiences about gods covenant with moses on 
mount sinai 
on aug 2 the pope said god selected jews as the chosen people 
on condition that they remained faithful to his law 
but the history of the old testament shows many instances of 
israels infidelity to god he said hence god sent the prophets 
as his messengers to call the people to conversion to warn them of 
their hardness of heart and to foretell a new covenant still to 
come 
the antidefamation league of bnai brith protested expressing 
profound concern at the comments and said it hoped the clock 
of catholicjewish relations has not been tragically set back 
the group said the popes remarks suggested the new covenant with 
christianity had replaced and superseded the alliance with jews who 
believe that gods covenant with them is everlasting 
jewish leaders said the popes remarks contradicted the second 
vatican councils 1965 document nostra aetate in our times which 
officially rescinded the accusation that the jews killed christ 
that document is considered a turning point in catholicjewish 
relations 
the rev pier francesco fumagalli an official of the vaticans 
office for relations with jews confirmed he received the 
antidefamation leagues letter of protest and said it would be 
studied otherwise the vatican has not commented publicly on the 
issue 
