federal engineers say they are stepping up 
their investigation into complaints that as many as 15 million 
nissan cars manufactured between 1982 and 1984 have a dangerous 
seating defect 
the national highway traffic safety administration said tuesday 
that it had received 96 complaints that the cars seat backs shifted 
backward suddenly and without warning 
the agency considers the allegations serious enough to upgrade a 
preliminary evaluation into an engineering analysis said spokesman 
tim hurd the change means engineers will study actual seat backs to 
determine whether they are defective as opposed to paperwork 
analysis 
nissan spokesman don spetner said the company was reviewing the 
decision and would have no immediate comment 
