the small business administration is 
overhauling its minority setaside program in response to the 
wedtech bribery and influencepeddling scandal 
the regulations issued tuesday and effective immediately put 
into effect legislation signed nine months ago by president reagan 
they are designed to minimize political influence on the agencys 
21yearold program under which companies owned by blacks 
hispanics asians indians and economically disadvantaged women are 
given preference in the awarding of government contracts 
among the changes 
the director of the program will be a career employee of the 
agency rather than a political appointee sba administrator susan 
engeleiter named erline patrick a former staff aide to the senate 
small business committee to the post 
the person in charge will not have to respond as much to the 
political pressures patrick said 
companies that misrepresent their status as minorityowned will 
be subject to stiffer penalties the maximum fine was increased from 
50000 to 500000 and the top jail term from five years to 10 
years 
for the first time competitive bidding is required among 
minorityowned companies for manufacturing contracts over 5 million 
and product and service contracts over 3 million 
the length of time a company may get special preference was 
lengthened from seven years to nine years but companies will be 
expected to derive a steadily decreasing percentage of their 
revenues from contracts awarded under the program 
owners of eligible companies must have net worth of less than 
250000 excluding equity in their home or business when they 
enter the program the old standard was 750000 including home or 
business equity 
the agency must rule on applications within 90 days 
patrick at a news conference said about 3000 companies 
participate she said the net worth requirement and the initiation 
of competitive bidding may discourage new participants but she said 
she hoped the deadline for decisions would boost participation 
when congress passed the law last year sen dale bumpers 
dark chairman of the senate small business committee said it was 
aimed at preventing the recurrence of wedtechtype scandals 
wedtech corp a south bronx military contractor was awarded 
more than 250 million in nobid contracts in just four years but 
became the subject of five different state and federal criminal 
investigations 
e robert wallach a san francisco lawyer and close friend of 
former us attorney general edwin meese was convicted earlier this 
month of illegally receiving 425000 from wedtech to influence 
government officials in the companys bids for contracts 
rep robert garcia dny faces trial next month on charges he 
and his wife illegally accepted cash and jewelry from wedtech 
