the us representative from houston had always fought on behalf 
of people in need but in 1983 he toured ethiopia and was shaken by 
the desolation and deprivation he saw visited upon the people there 
when he returned to washington leland began his crusade to 
create a select committee on hunger that committee with leland 
at its head has been the conscience of the hill not just 
concerning famine relief for ethiopia but the plight of the poor in 
the united states 
the impetus behind the formation of the hunger committee was a 
trip to an ethopian refugee camp where a little girl died before 
his eyes from the hunger that consumed her it was on his fifth trip 
to such refugee camps that his plane crashed 
the tributes to him from president bush from house speaker 
thomas foley from activist jesse jackson go properly to one who in 
foleys words represented the best in compassion that we as a 
nation possess 
real tribute to mickey leland will come as such leaders work to 
ensure that a commitment to feed the hungry is always a top priority 
of this land of plenty 
