new yorks highest court agreed wednesday to 
hear the appeals of three white men convicted in the 1986 howard 
beach attack in which a black man fleeing a white gang was hit by a 
car and killed 
state court of appeals judge joseph bellacosa on behalf of the 
full sevenmember court granted the appeals of scott kern jon 
lester and jason ladone 
kern and lester both 20 and ladone 18 were convicted in 
december 1987 of seconddegree manslaughter and firstdegree assault 
for attacking three black men in the howard beach section of the new 
york city borough of queens on dec 20 1986 
one of the black men 23yearold michael griffith was struck by 
a car and killed as he fled another man cedric sandiford was 
beaten with tree limbs and a baseball bat 
the cas is likely to reach the top court late this year or early 
next year said court of appeals spokesman walter mordaunt 
lester who is in jail was sentenced to 15 to 30 years in 
prison he also was sentenced to one to three years in prison on an 
unrelated prior conviction for weapons possession 
kern was sentenced to a six to 18year term and is out on 
300000 bail ladone was sentenced to five to 15 years and is out 
on 150000 bail both had their sentences stayed pending the appeal 
bellacosa granted the appeal without comment by agreeing to hear 
the case bellacosa feels there are questions of law that should be 
decided upon by the top court said mordaunt 
helman brook an assistant to special state prosecutor charles 
hynes had no comment on bellacosas decision to grant the appeal 
charles weintraub lawyer for all three defendants said hed 
base the new appeal on many of the same arguments he used 
unsuccessfully before the appellate division of state supreme court 
in july the appellate division unanimously upheld the 
convictions and sentences 
