each of the b2s four engines has an accessory drive one out 
of the four drives indicated low oil pressure sjaardema said 
each accessory drive is like a transmission connected to each 
engine by a shaft the drives power air turbine starters and 
hydraulic systems sjaardema said 
air turbine starters are used to restart engines the b2s 
hydraulics apparently control its landing gear but it isnt known 
if they are used to move flaps and other control surfaces as is the 
case on many planes tech sgt donn clarius said there was no 
failure of the hydraulic system 
the air force had planned to fly the plane shortly after dawn 
tuesday but the test was rescheduled for wednesday because of 
delays caused by wind and a long list of preflight checks officials 
said 
the air force tried to fly the b2 for the first time on july 15 
