<TEXT>
many who lost loved ones in the nations 
secondworst air disaster fear theyll relive the tragedy when 
liability suits come to trial in october said a member of a support 
group for relatives of crash victims 
northwest flight 255 crashed at detroit metropolitan airport in 
suburban romulus on the hot humid night of aug 16 1987 killing 
154 people on board and two people on the ground 
the jet failed to gain altitude during takeoff and slammed into 
an overpass on interstate 94 the sole survivor was cecelia cichan 
then 4 
the little girl is living with her aunt and uncle rita and frank 
lumpkin in birmingham ala shielded from media inquiries she 
lost her mother father and 6yearold brother in the crash 
about 300 people family and friends of the dead met on a grassy 
hillside overlooking middlebelt road at interstate 94 where the 
jetliner broke apart in flames moments after takeoff 
as long as some of us can manage to walk up that hill we will 
