<TEXT>
atlantic richfield co plans to market a 
leadfree gasoline for older cars and trucks that use leaded gas and 
said the new fuel could cut pollution from such vehicles by up to 15 
percent 
the gasoline will go on sale next month at 750 arco stations in 
southern california for about the same price as leaded regular 
gasoline arco said tuesday 
the announcement came the same day the california air resources 
board unanimously adopted a sweeping 20year plan to clean southern 
californias air the nations dirtiest it will transform the way 
californians work and play 
arcos new gasoline was created to reduce pollution caused by the 
estimated 12 million worstpolluting vehicles in the region cars 
made before 1975 and trucks built before 1980 
arcos refinery in carson will produce the gasoline which is 
called ec1 for emission control1 and cost about 20 million to 
develop 
were making this heavy investment because we believe the 
dominant fuel of the future will be gasoline rather than the 
alternatives youve been hearing about said lodwrick m cook 
arco chairman and chief executive officer those alternatives 
include methanol and natural gas 
what we hope to demonstrate today is that we can clean up 
gasoline cook said 
the fuel has an octane level of 88 and contains methyl tertiary 
butyl ether which arco spokesman al greenstein described as an 
oxygenated additive 
the mtbe is what makes up for the loss of octane by eliminating 
the lead he said its something thats on the market that 
wasnt available a few years ago 
arco officials said the fuel reduces chemical components that 
cause smog by about onethird and benzene a cancercausing 
pollutant by half the fuelsulfur content was reduced by 80 
percent 
were pleased that arco has taken the initiative in developing 
a new gasoline that is more environmentally acceptable and which 
reflects the direction of the air resources boards future 
regulation said board chairwoman jananne sharpless 
the board tuesday voted 80 to adopt the smogcontrol plan 
despite industry objections the plan will strangle the regions 
economy it will target emissions from everything from motor 
vehicles factories and auto paint to dry cleaners bakeries 
aerosol cans and backyard grills 
the plan embraces landuse planning transportation programs and 
stricter industry standards it was completed in march by the south 
coast air quality management district and the southern california 
association of governments 
regional air quality officials estimate that the plan will cost 
26 billion a year business interests say annual costs will reach 
12 billion 
enactment was hailed as a leap into a brave new world by 
harriet wieder an orange county supervisor on the ninemember air 
resources board 
the plan was branded texas justice by william t huston a 
developer leading a coalition of business and labor interests 
fighting to revise the plane theyre acting as their own judge 
jury and executioner he said 
