merv griffin the entertainer who purchased the company last year 
from developer donald trump 
state gaming regulators will hold hearings next month to consider 
whether resorts has enough financial stability to change griffins 
interim authorization into a license 
resorts based here will have to pay more than 130 million in 
interest and principal this year but its operations likely will not 
generate enough money to cover that in 1988 the companys cash 
flow was only 602 million 
according to figures issued monday resorts posted a 279 
million net loss for the second quarter of 1989 compared to a 138 
million net loss for the same period in 1988 
for the first six months of 1989 the company reported a net loss 
of 466 million compared to a 176 million net loss for last 
years first half 
resorts earnings from operations for the second quarter were 
reported at 411000 compared to 89 million for the same period 
last year earnings from operations for the first six months were 
61 million compared to 129 million for the 1988 first half 
in a filing with the securities and exchange commission resorts 
blamed shrinking revenue at its atlantic city casino on fewer bets 
wagered by patrons 
the transitional state of the companys marketing efforts 
contributed to this as did the fact that during the second quarter 
portions of the casino were out of service due to renovations 
said a statement by a public relations firm for the gaming and real 
estate company 
resorts also cited lower revenues at its paradise island casino 
because of a significant decrease in the table game hold 
percentage the ratio of casino win to the total amount of chips 
purchased 
some news about resorts future plans will come at a bondholders 
meeting here set for sept 19 company executives said they will 
