a shipping company and a tanker captain 
pleaded guilty today to federal charges of causing a 300000gallon 
oil spill off rhode island on june 23 and agreed to pay fines 
totaling 510000 
ballard shipping co a liberianregistered company operating in 
piraeus greece agreed to pay 500000 to the state for 
environmental research the captain iakovos georgudis a 
43yearold greek citizen agreed to a 10000 fine 
each pleaded guilty to a misdemeanor violation of the federal 
clean water act 
nearly 300000 gallons of heating oil spilled into the mouth of 
narragansett bay off newport when the tanker world prodigy ran 
aground 
if convicted the captain could have received a year in jail and 
a penalty equal to twice the amount of damage the coast guard has 
estimated the cleanup cost alone at 2 million the shipping company 
was also liable for twice the damage 
the captain also is under indictment on state charges carrying up 
to a year and a month in jail and fines of 20000 
us attorney lincoln almond said he did not press for harsher 
penalties because the spill resulted from simple negligence 
the captain became distracted and was also doing computations 
to double check estimates involving the unloading of the oil 
almond said 
we believe it was about a six or sevenminute lapse and there 
was nothing in advance of that that was not done properly 
he was simply trying to handle more than one person could 
handle at one time said peter dibiase georgudis attorney 
georgudis who had no comment after todays federal court 
hearing previously told the governor and coast guard officials that 
he failed to turn the vessel in time to avoid the reef 
he also admitted no harbor pilot was on board to take the tanker 
