<TEXT>
an airplane parts distributor and its president 
pleaded guilty today to selling thousands of used nuts and bolts as 
new to several airlines and aerospace contractors 
rice aircraft inc of hauppauge ny and its president bruce j 
rice 42 pleaded guilty to conspiracy and mail fraud 
the fasteners hold together everything from wings to engines and 
were distributed widely in the aerospace industry from 1977 through 
1988 mostly in the early 1980s authorities said 
us attorney gene wilson said federal investigators have not 
directly linked the parts to any aircraft crashes 
wilson said rice aircraft had the parts secretly stripped and 
replated or relubricated and then sold them as new 
rice could receive up to five years in prison fines of 500000 
and court costs of 250000 at sentencing feb 16 the company faces 
fines up to 50000 and will share with rice in possible restitution 
up to 1 million 
the guilty pleas came as the government charged three more 
defendants with paying kickbacks and conspiring to underbid on 
airplane parts contracts 
