government the israeli government airbus british aerospace 
grumman sikorsky martin marietta boeing helicopters air france 
united airlines the brazilian airline varig twa american airlines 
and pan am 
some parts were purchased for military aircraft including the 
f111 the b1b bomber and f14 fighters wilson said 
the us attorneys also office filed charges against richard k 
ohlman 70 of mission viejo calif accusing him of acting as a 
middleman who conspired with rice and rice aircraft to pay kickbacks 
in 1982 to boeing surplus personnel 
the kickbacks were paid to help rice aircraft sell the recycled 
parts to boeing surplus a unit of the boeing co authorities said 
in exchange for the kickbacks wilson said ohlman was given the 
last look at competitors secret bids 
unrelated charges also were filed against former boeing surplus 
employees john j rockwood 49 of bellevue wash and richard k 
watson 66 of los angeles 
